<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 02 at 1:17AM CDT until May 02 at 1:45AM CDT by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 145 AM CDT
FOR NORTH CENTRAL ERATH AND SOUTHERN PALO PINTO COUNTIES...
At 116 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Gordon, or 15
miles northeast of Ranger, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Gordon, Strawn and Mingus.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
